      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09D\",\"process_rule\":\"1. Copy the decision table entries into table `J09D_temp` only for tours that start with `J09D`.\\n\\n2. Add the column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to table `J09D_temp`.\\n\\n3. Classify the meter reading type in `ENTSCHEIDUNG`:\\n   - if a `HAUS` has less than 3 `EQUNR`, set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `KSA`\\n   - else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `EVU`\\n\\n4. JOIN the working table with `EABLG` using `INSTALLATION`.\\n\\n5. JOIN the working table with `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER` using `EQUNR`.\\n\\n6. Compare customer data from `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER`.\\n\\n7. If sales customer data is not empty:\\n   1. Use the `SALES_MASTER` customer table entries.\\n   Else:\\n   1. Use the `NET_MASTER` customer table entries.\\n\\n8. Export the final table as CSV file named `J09D` using exactly these column names:\\n   `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`\\n\\n9. Send an email to `meter.readings@evu.com` with the exported CSV file attached. Use file path: `<path_to_exported_csv_file>`.\\n\\n10. Delete the temporary table.\"}",
            "id": "lc_f88eed75-81ef-469a-8ed8-8a8049626c1d"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "7d714798-c439-4738-8fd4-b1cfbfd0baa8",
        "tool_call_id": "call_kwsqDUbkcgSZkJxOEbhChXQd",
        "artifact": {
          "structured_content": {
            "success": true,
            "process_rule_id": "J09D",
            "process_rule": "1. Copy the decision table entries into table `J09D_temp` only for tours that start with `J09D`.\n\n2. Add the column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to table `J09D_temp`.\n\n3. Classify the meter reading type in `ENTSCHEIDUNG`:\n   - if a `HAUS` has less than 3 `EQUNR`, set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `KSA`\n   - else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `EVU`\n\n4. JOIN the working table with `EABLG` using `INSTALLATION`.\n\n5. JOIN the working table with `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER` using `EQUNR`.\n\n6. Compare customer data from `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER`.\n\n7. If sales customer data is not empty:\n   1. Use the `SALES_MASTER` customer table entries.\n   Else:\n   1. Use the `NET_MASTER` customer table entries.\n\n8. Export the final table as CSV file named `J09D` using exactly these column names:\n   `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`\n\n9. Send an email to `meter.readings@evu.com` with the exported CSV file attached. Use file path: `<path_to_exported_csv_file>`.\n\n10. Delete the temporary table."
          }
        },
        "status": "success"
      }
    },
